<p>When I want to check which Pandas dataframe is being called, how do I use the dataframe name in an if condition?</p>  <p>I keep getting "The truth value of a DataFrame is ambiguous...." and can't figure out a way around it.</p>  <pre><code>df_even = pd.DataFrame( data=[2,4,6,12,64,866,222]) df_prime = pd.DataFrame( data=[5,7,11,13,17,19])  df_list = [df_even, df_prime]  for frame in df_list:     if frame == df_even:         name = 'even'     elif frame == df_prime:         name = 'prime'     # do something with the dataframe next </code></pre>